HEADWORD: Heliozoa
<hw>He`li*o*zo"a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <?/ the sun + <grk>zw^,on</grk> an animal.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>An order of fresh-water rhizopods having a more or less globular
form, with slender radiating pseudopodia; the sun animalcule.</def></p>

